Qualifiers.Applicability: Entryways that are vaulted and recessed beyond the house facade and roof
Qualifiers.Exclusions: Non-vaulted entryways or those not recessed

Dimensional: Intersection of front facade and top of roof material at ridge
Material: Outside material of the entryway feature

Procedures: The area is measured to the outside material of the entryway feature
The area counts TWICE toward gross floor area if the entryway is vaulted

Mandatory: The area is measured to the outside material of the entryway feature
Conditional logic: If the entryway is considered to be a vaulted entryway, the area will be counted TWICE

Special cases: A portion of the entryway is recessed beyond the house facade and roof. It is included in the area that counts.

Logical dependencies: The area counts TWICE toward gross floor area if the entryway is vaulted
